oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: National Barn Dance - WLS performances - 1941-03-29
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Home recorded National Barn Dance performances, featuring Prairie Ramblers, Prairie Sweethearts, Arkie The Arkansas Woodchopper, The Westerners, and Louise Massey on March 29, 1941 on radio station WLS (Chicago, IL).
